#12405
nameless clockmaker~
the clockmaker~
The nameless clockmaker sits in the shadows here.
~
He looks to be older than even the very tower he occupies here.  His garment is
made up of old white cloth wrapped about himself, his long gray beard barely
poking through along with the rest of his face.  He seems to be a very
intelligent person, probably very knowledgeable, it could serve you well to ask
him about many things in the world, if you know how to ask him correctly.
~
1073741827 0 0 C
55 0 0 32700d1+0 0d0+0
0 0
108 108 1
13 13 13 13 13 13 13
0 0 0 0 0
88 5 0 0 0 1 0
0 0 0 0 10240 0 0 0
> speech_prog graveyard? graveyard. graveyard~
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'So, you want to know about the graveyard do you?  I can tell you much of it.  You see, I was walking these lands back before it was even built, and the now ruined cathedral stood taller and mightier than the greatest building around here now days, believe you me.  One particularly dark day, a dragon concieved from the purest of evils appeared and simply grinded it into the very pile of rubble it lays as today.  As for the dragon, it flew off, to a floating island I tell you.  And for the graveyard now?  Well, that cathedral was marked with evil, there is a hole there, and should you truely be courageous and of good spirirt, or wish to find great treasures, then go down there to bare witness to it's many unspeakable horrors, and conquer them to cleanse it of evil once and for all.'
~
> speech_prog cathedral? cathedral. cathedral~
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'Well now, that cathedral is very old.  It was once a shining tribute to the gods, but was destroyed by an evil dragon who I swaer came down from a floating island.  After it was destroyed, it was turned into a cemetary, kind of fitting to match the gloom of the whole occassion, don't you think?  But that graveyard still stands there, off to the northwest part of town.  And you know what else?  That is the source of another perverse evil now days, but that relates more to the tombstones...'
~
> speech_prog tombstones? tombstone? tombstones. tombstone. tombstones tombstone~
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'Yes, those tombstones, at the graveyard.  Well, that cemetary happens to be sitting right next to the western plains.  As a result of this and the evil that now hangs over the old cathedral, skeletons and such forms of undead can be seen roaming those plains, even in the middle of the day!  I feel sorry for them, very much.  I knew many of them possibly and they were good men and women, not deserving of this fate in the least.  Perhaps if one was to travel down into the earth and find the source of this, then they could be set free.  That person would be a true hero indeed.'
~
> speech_prog skeletons? skeleton? skeletons. skeleton. skeletons skeleton~
'Well, those are undead peoples, just like you and me.  Once they were anyways.
'I suppose it would be better to ask about the tombstones then of them.
~
> speech_prog dragons? dragons. dragons. dragon. dragons dragon~
'Ah yes, that miserable beast.  Swept down one day from the skies and destroyed
'out precious cathedral, which is now the graveyard site.  People wonder about
'that thing, but I know better.  He came from a floating island in the sky.
~
> speech_prog island? island. island~
'Ah yes, the floating island.  The one thing even I don't know much about.
'I do know this though.  It's the home of a flying dragon.  I'm not talking
'about your ordinary dragon race or creature here, I mean a REAL dragon.  One
'of about the evilest you can get.  The other is that if you wanted a glimpse
'of it, the best place I can think of would be to climb up the mountains to the
'west, there's a peak there that I bet you could get a view across the world
'from, not to mention an island in the sky.
~
> speech_prog town? town. town~
'So you're wondering about this here town are you?  Well, not a lot to say
'about it, not by me anyways.  I keep to myself here really.  If you want to
'learn about the town, best thing would be to ask someone younger, like my
'associate here, she comes at noon to keep things here in order while I go
'home.
~
> speech_prog church? church. church~
'Are you interested in that church?  Well, I'm not truthfully.  It's nothing
'like the old cathedral which used to be where the graveyard is now.  But I'll
'say this, since that church was built it was made into the paladins guild.
'I wonder why no one has wondered about that second floor even though there's
'no apparent way up to it?
if class($n) == Paladin
'You're a paladin, aren't ya?  I'll tell you what to do, go behind the alter.
'If the gods find you worthy then you will pass through a holy light to the
'very back.  There you'll be able to get up to the second floor.  Good luck.
else
'Doesn't matter anyways, to get there you are under the judgement of the gods
'and they wouldn't find anyone "worthy" of getting over there unless they were
'a paladin themself.
endif
~
> speech_prog towers? tower? towers. tower. towers tower~
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'So, these here towers huh?  Well, I'm not allowed to tell you about this here tower.  Why?  I can't tell you that either.  Ha!'
chuckle
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'I can tell you, I suppose, that they both have higher purposes then what they really appear to have.  Straight to the north is Tower Steel, this here is Tower CLockworks.  I tell you to be careful poking you nose around like this though, otherwise you might end up, well, like me.  You really think I'm allowed to leave this place?'
cackle
~
> speech_prog warriors? warrior? warriors. warrior. warriors warrior~
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'Warriors eh?  Only thing that really comes to mind mentioning that is those blasted warriors down at the town inn.  I've had my own encounter with them, gave the mean one the scar across his face myself actually.'
smile
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'He's half-orc you know?  If you speak the language then that helps, but the one thing is that they don't take kindly to anyone who isn't a warrior, they are big on guild stuff.  That door they're guarding is the warrior guild.  To get in you gotta make friendly with them, especially the mean one.  I'd go ask the bartender about them if you're that interested, that and about the door too.  I bet he knows something about that door that he's just waiting to tell somebody.'
~
> speech_prog garlac? garlac. garlac~
'Why, you know Garlac over at the alchemy shop?  I'll be damned.  He's a good
'old friend of mine, but I'm much, much older.  He's very sick now days, and I
'haven't seen him in ages.  I can only hope he gets better soon.  If you tell
'him you know me, he might be inclined to give you a little something every
'now and then, but don't count on that.
~
> speech_prog ogres? ogre? ogres. ogre. ogres ogre~
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'Can't find your way to the land of ogres?  There is a key ogre area, and it is closer then you might think.  Head out far into the eastern plains, there is a rather large forest that runs along the north.  The entrance you'll be looking for is upon a hill actually.'
~
> greet_prog 100~
mpecho _lbl The clockmaker says 'Welcome to my humble place.  It's not big I'm afraid, so not many people can fit in here at a time.  I am very old, and know a lot from my travels and age.  You can ask me about many things at anytime, though I don't know much about this here town, since it's pretty new, though you can ask my apprentice about such things when she comes at morning.'
~
> rand_prog 1~
mpecho The clockmaker picks a gear off of a shelf, examines it for a second, then puts it back on the shelf with a sigh.
~
> time_prog 0~
mpat 12491 mpecho The clockmaker arrives from the north.
mptransfer clockmaker 12491
'Hello my dear, I trust you've had an uneventful day.
~
> act_prog p Erin nods in agreement with you.~
'Ah, good, good.  You may leave now, I'll take over here.
mptransfer erin 11288
mpat 11288 mpforce erin mpat 12491 mpecho Erin leaves north.
'Now, what can I do for you?
~
> time_prog 12~
yawn
'well it is time for me to leave, my associate will arrive soon I'm sure.
mptransfer clockmaker 11288
mpat 12491 mpecho The clockmaker leaves north.
~
