> act_prog p gives you a wedding band.~
'Very well, I shall engrave this for you now.
if goldamt($n) > 4999
'I will require the payment of 5000 gold for this service, of course.
mpforce $n give 5000 coins iptarius
'thank you
mpecho Iptarius gets engraving tools from his inventory chest, and immediatly begins to skillfully engrave the wedding band.
mposet wedding short a wedding band from $n
mposet weddin long A wedding band is here, please return it to $n if it's lost.
'Ah...one of my finest pieces of work yet.  I hope you find it to your satisfaction, $n.
give wedding $n
mpecho Iptarius returns his engraving tools to his inventory chest.
else
'My fee for engravement of wedding bands is 5000, please come back when you have enough gold.
give wedding $n
endif
~
> act_prog p gives you a wedding band from~
'Sorry, but this has already been engraved.
give wedding $n
~
> bribe_prog 1~
'Thank you for your contribution, though I hardly know what to do with it.
~
> speech_prog wedding? wedding. wedding~
'Yes, we sell special-order wedding bands, which are a great way to display your love for your spouse.  The price for one wedding band comes to 10000 gold coins total.  We also do
engraving with your name attached to it for an additional 5000 gold coins.  You and your partner can each get one and exchange, that way everyone can know who you're married to.
'As a warning, remember that wedding bands are for people who are married, and therefor can only be used by level 50 and above in accordance with state law.
'If you're interested, just say "I would like to buy one"
~
> speech_prog p I would like to buy one~
if goldamt($n) > 9999
'Allright, that will be 10000 gold coins.
mpforce $n give 10000 coins iptarius
'Thank you, and here is your wedding band, gift wrapped for no extra charge.
smile
mpoload 12472 50
mpoload 12473 1
put wedding package
close package
give package $n
else
'I'm sorry, but our wedding bands go for 10000 gold coins.  Please come back when you have enough money.
endif
~
> speech_prog engraving? engraved? engrave? engraving. engraved. engrave. engraving engraved engrave~
'The way engraving works is you give me your already bought wedding band, and I will put your name on it permanently.  You then would give this band to your spouse, and they give one they themself had engraved to you...an exchange of wedding bands.
'The process will cost 5000 gold coins to payed before I do the work..but don't worry, I'll have you hand that over after you've given me the band.
~
